# v0.0.1

Initial version of scx-adapt.
- It includes:
    - YAML profile configuration parsing-running,
    - Creating traces of sched_ext,
    - Creating CSV logs of system data (load avg. and pressures etc.),
    - Systemd profile for scx-adapt,
    - Managing profiles in /etc/scx-adapt/profiles

[X] Fix YAML unmarshalling and checks
[X] Fix running profiles logic
[X] Write unit tests for functions
[X] Add wait_time to YAML config
[X] Ordering scheds by priorities and conflict checking in YAML config
[X] Profile runner function
[X] Profile runner state file (readonly)
[X] `add-profile` (to `/etc/scx-adapt`), `rm-profile`, `start-profile` (from /etc if, not absolute path or not in cwd), status helpers and commands
[X] Commands' explanations and auto-completion
[X] Turn to system scheduler if any scx satisfies criterias
[X] Fix test cases in order to work with new file structure (obj's for testing to `tests/obj` folder)
[X] Add logging to CLI
[X] Add list-profiles command
[X] README file
[X] Add function descriptions
[X] Systemd service file (which takes yaml templates)
[X] Add `install-service` and `remove-service` commands
[X] Automated go tests in Github Actions

